Subject:    <a href="?t=95837890400015&r=1&w=2">Mailing list domain - MX records only?</a>
From:       <a href="?a=95837785600020&r=1&w=2">stjohns () beast ! DDN ! MIL (Mike St !  Johns)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198809">1988-09-10 16:42:00</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837783026950&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837783026950&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I had kind of a strange thought - one of the biggest hassles about
sending to mailing lists is finding out where they are kep in the
first place.  This means FTPing the 3 files from the nic and pawing
through them, and then hoping these files are up to date.

What would the impact be of creating a domain  ("Mail.LIST"?)
consisting of nothing but MX records pointing to mailing lists?  So
instead of TCP-IP@sri-nic.arpa, I could send to TCP-IP@mail.list and
still have it delivered.  

Mike

